ownedComment.body: There is an attribute "validityStatus" in Validity, which is madatory but not sufficient for traffic regulation orders. Since the attribute is mandatory, the attribute should be set to the following values. If the "status" is "madeAndImplemented", "madeButNotImplemented" and "madeAndPartiallyImplemented" use "active" as the value of the "validityStatus" attribute. If the "status" is "planned" use "planned" as the value of "validityStatus". If the "status" is "partiallyWithdrawn" or "withdrawn" use "suspended".

Calendar weeks start with Monday. First week is the week containing the first of the month.
Week in month defines each 7 day period in the month, with each week starting on the day of the week of the first day of the month.

Within each instance of this class, specific enumerated values can only be used once for all attributes. e.g. applicableMonth can only contain "january" once. A combination of applicableDay "monday" and "tuesday" and applicableMonth "may" and "june" results in a data set of all Mondays and Tuesdays in May and June.
timePeriodOfDay and dayOfWeek must be applicable within the specified overall time period or exception period respectively.
exceptionPeriod is a period during which validity is suspended and must be applicable within the specified overallTimePeriod.
When using this class, at least one "applicableDay" must be specified in class "DayWeekMonth".
